<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-11-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-11-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="534" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d534">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Herbert</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">British
                                        Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-11-02"><hi rend="italic">November 2,
                                1892</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your note of the 24th
                            September last I have the honor in accordance with instructions which I
                            have received from my Government to transmit for your information copy
                            of a dispatch which has been addressed by the Earl of Rosebery to Her
                            Majesty’s consul in Samoa, containing instructions for his guidance with
                            respect to the audit of the accounts of the municipality and the Samoan
                            Government.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Michael H.
                            Herbert.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>